---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About — Jimmy P. Le">
  <div slot="aside">
    <div class="aside-block">
      <h2 class="aside-label">Availability</h2>
      <p>
        Open to software, ML, and NLP engineering roles.
        DC / Northern Virginia preferred; remote considered.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="aside-block">
      <h2 class="aside-label">Reach me</h2>
      <ul class="aside-contact-list">
        <li>
          <span class="contact-method">Email — fastest</span>
          <a href="mailto:lejp3@vcu.edu">lejp3@vcu.edu</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="contact-method">GitHub</span>
          <a href="https://github.com/jimmyphuocle">jimmyphuocle</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="contact-method">LinkedIn</span>
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jimmy-le-vcu/">jimmy-le-vcu</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="contact-method">Google Scholar</span>
          <a href="https://scholar.google.com">Profile</a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="prose">
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p>
      I'm Jimmy P. Le. I'm a PhD student in Computer Science
      at Virginia Commonwealth University, where I work in the Natural Language Processing Lab
      under Dr. Bridget McInnes. My current research focuses on triple
      filtration in GraphRAG for explainable biomedical question
      answering, integrating Literature-Based Discovery strategies into
      retrieval pipelines over UMLS-derived knowledge graphs.
    </p>
    <p>
      Outside of research, I work as a Network Operations Center analyst
      at VCU Infrastructure Services. Before VCU, I held an IT Team Lead
      role at Wichita State University.
    </p>
    <p>
      I'm currently exploring software, ML, and NLP engineering roles —
      ideally in or near the DC / Northern Virginia area. If you're
      hiring or want to talk about biomedical NLP, GraphRAG, or
      retrieval failure modes, I'd love to hear from you.
    </p>

    <h2>Currently</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Running ablation experiments on the LBD-GraphRAG project across multiple retrieval conditions</li>
      <li>Building a Biomedical NLP API portfolio project with FastAPI and Hugging Face Transformers</li>
      <li>Working through NeetCode 150 for technical interviews</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
